    "course_title": "PRINCIPLES OF X-RAY COMPUTED TOMOGRAPHY",
    "description": "Understand the basic principles of x-ray computed tomography (CT), and how to think when a technical problem arises in CT. Accomplished through a review of the history of CT developments and key components of CT systems, lectures on various CT reconstruction algorithms, image quality, and radiation dose, origin and correction methods of various CT artifacts.",
